Description:
Quite Court Location and So Close to Everything
The Feel:
You get the feel as soon as you drive into the cute court then turning onto the north side of the street to enter this very cute cottage gives you the natural feeling it's a warm and cosy home offering so much future potential or an idyllic little beauty to keep the way it currently is. The high timber ceiling providing character and space in the lounge, kitchen and dining areas offer a beautiful charm.
The Facts:
- 3 BR home on 585sqm approx. in highly sought-after pocket of Barwon Heads;
- North facing backyard with a gorgeous establishment of neighbouring trees providing a forest feeling;
- Split system heating and cooling in the lounge room and master bedroom;
- Spacious lounge room adjacent to the kitchen and dining area;
- Large garage in the backyard providing ample storage space to accomodate all your toys;
- Ideal location, destined to continue with a lot of capital growth;
- Plenty of upside to renovate further and/or extend if you have the creative flare to add some more magic to it;
- Walk to the Village Park, beach, Barwon Heads Primary & Hitchcock Avenue
The Owner Loves.
The location, the backyard, the cute cottage feel, the neighbours and how quiet the street is, these are hard to find in the market and that's why we snapped up when we bought it
* The property is currently leased on a 'month by month' agreement at $410pw with Bellarine Property as the managing agency. Vacant Possession can be secured or alternatively you can continue as a landlord and keep the tenants.
